{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to take you\non a journey very quickly."},{"time":2278,"text":"To explain the wish, I'm going\nto have to take you somewhere"},{"time":5151,"text":"where many people haven't been,\nand that's around the world."},{"time":8004,"text":"When I was about 24 years old, Kate Stohr\nand myself started an organization"},{"time":12137,"text":"to get architects and designers\ninvolved in humanitarian work,"},{"time":15801,"text":"not only about responding\nto natural disasters,"},{"time":18468,"text":"but involved in systemic issues."},{"time":21436,"text":"We believe that where the resources\nand expertise are scarce,"},{"time":26039,"text":"innovative, sustainable design can really\nmake a difference in people's lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32118,"text":"So I started my life as an architect,\nor training as an architect,"},{"time":37043,"text":"and I was always interested\nin socially responsible design,"},{"time":40484,"text":"and how you can really make an impact."},{"time":42400,"text":"But when I went to architecture school,"},{"time":44370,"text":"it seemed that I was\na black sheep in the family."},{"time":47345,"text":"Many architects seemed to think\nthat when you design,"},{"time":50036,"text":"you design a jewel, and it's a jewel\nthat you try and crave for;"},{"time":53841,"text":"whereas I felt that when you design,"},{"time":55802,"text":"you either improve\nor you create a detriment"},{"time":58481,"text":"to the community\nin which you're designing."},{"time":60568,"text":"So you're not just doing\na building for the residents"},{"time":63100,"text":"or for the people who are going to use it,\nbut for the community as a whole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66703,"text":"And in 1999, we started by responding\nto the issue of the housing crisis"},{"time":73153,"text":"for returning refugees in Kosovo."},{"time":75188,"text":"And I didn't know what I was doing --\nlike I said, mid-20s --"},{"time":78824,"text":"and I'm the Internet generation,\nso we started a website."},{"time":83397,"text":"We put a call out there,\nand to my surprise, in a couple of months,"},{"time":86910,"text":"we had hundreds of entries\nfrom around the world."},{"time":90132,"text":"That led to a number\nof prototypes being built"},{"time":92329,"text":"and really experimenting with some ideas."},{"time":95272,"text":"Two years later we started doing a project"},{"time":97427,"text":"on developing mobile health clinics\nin sub-Saharan Africa,"},{"time":101085,"text":"responding to the HIV/AIDS pandemic."},{"time":105418,"text":"That led to 550 entries from 53 countries."},{"time":111826,"text":"We also have designers\nfrom around the world that participate."},{"time":116600,"text":"And we had an exhibit\nof work that followed that."},{"time":120270,"text":"2004 was the tipping point for us."},{"time":122708,"text":"We started responding to natural disasters"},{"time":124753,"text":"and getting involved in Iran, in Bam,"},{"time":127398,"text":"also following up on our work in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130122,"text":"Working within the United States --"},{"time":131994,"text":"most people look at poverty\nand they see the face of a foreigner."},{"time":135089,"text":"But I live in Bozeman, Montana --"},{"time":137187,"text":"go up to the north plains\non the reservations,"},{"time":139429,"text":"or go down to Alabama\nor Mississippi, pre-Katrina,"},{"time":142878,"text":"and I could have shown you\nplaces that have far worse conditions"},{"time":145934,"text":"than many developing countries\nthat I've been to."},{"time":148264,"text":"So we got involved in and worked\nin inner cities and elsewhere;"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151776,"text":"and also, I will go into\nsome more projects."},{"time":155217,"text":"2005: Mother Nature kicked our ass."},{"time":158135,"text":"I think we can pretty much assume\nthat 2005 was a horrific year"},{"time":162912,"text":"when it comes to natural disasters."},{"time":164603,"text":"And because of the Internet,"},{"time":166117,"text":"and because of connections\nto blogs and so forth,"},{"time":169530,"text":"within literally hours of the tsunami,\nwe were already raising funds,"},{"time":174006,"text":"getting involved, working\nwith people on the ground."},{"time":177606,"text":"We run from a couple of laptops,\nand in the first couple of days,"},{"time":180812,"text":"I had 4,000 emails\nfrom people needing help."},{"time":183915,"text":"So we began to get involved\nin projects there,"},{"time":186812,"text":"and I'll talk about some others."},{"time":188450,"text":"And then of course, this year\nwe've been responding to Katrina,"},{"time":191445,"text":"as well as following up\non our reconstruction work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193913,"text":"So this is a brief overview."},{"time":196600,"text":"In 2004, I really couldn't manage\nthe number of people who wanted to help,"},{"time":201041,"text":"or the number of requests\nthat I was getting."},{"time":203170,"text":"It was all coming\ninto my laptop and cell phone."},{"time":205725,"text":"So we decided to embrace\nan open-source model of business --"},{"time":211122,"text":"so that anyone, anywhere in the world,\ncould start a local chapter,"},{"time":214313,"text":"and they can get involved\nin local problems."},{"time":216403,"text":"Because I believe there\nis no such thing as Utopia."},{"time":218838,"text":"All problems are local.\nAll solutions are local."},{"time":221434,"text":"So that means, you know,\nsomebody who's based in Mississippi"},{"time":226092,"text":"knows more about Mississippi than I do."},{"time":228469,"text":"So what happened is, we used Meetup\nand all these other Internet tools,"},{"time":234600,"text":"and we ended up having\n40 chapters starting up,"},{"time":238915,"text":"thousands of architects in 104 countries."},{"time":243008,"text":"So the bullet point --\nsorry, I never do a suit,"},{"time":246473,"text":"so I knew that I was going\nto take this off."},{"time":248892,"text":"OK, because I'm going to do it very quick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253203,"text":"This isn't just about nonprofit."},{"time":255250,"text":"What it showed me is that\nthere's a grassroots movement going on,"},{"time":258448,"text":"of socially responsible designers\nwho really believe"},{"time":261046,"text":"that this world has got a lot smaller,\nand that we have the opportunity --"},{"time":264982,"text":"not the responsibility,\nbut the opportunity --"},{"time":267162,"text":"to really get involved in making change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271665,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":276941,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280989,"text":"I'm adding that to my time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282812,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":285637,"text":"So what you don't know is,"},{"time":287600,"text":"we've got these thousands of designers\nworking around the world,"},{"time":290648,"text":"connected basically by a website,\nand we have a staff of three."},{"time":294504,"text":"The fact that nobody told us\nwe couldn't do it, we did it."},{"time":298942,"text":"And so there's something\nto be said about naïveté."},{"time":301314,"text":"So seven years later, we've developed"},{"time":303235,"text":"so that we've got advocacy,\ninstigation and implementation."},{"time":306673,"text":"We advocate for good design,\nnot only through student workshops"},{"time":310342,"text":"and lectures and public forums, op-eds;"},{"time":312688,"text":"we have a book on humanitarian work;"},{"time":314933,"text":"but also disaster mitigation\nand dealing with public policy."},{"time":318140,"text":"We can talk about FEMA,\nbut that's another talk."},{"time":322036,"text":"Instigation, developing ideas\nwith communities and NGOs,"},{"time":325420,"text":"doing open-source design competitions."},{"time":328272,"text":"Referring, matchmaking with communities."},{"time":330804,"text":"And then implementing -- actually\ngoing out there and doing the work,"},{"time":334135,"text":"because when you invent,\nit's never a reality until it's built."},{"time":340338,"text":"So it's really important\nthat if we're designing"},{"time":343103,"text":"and trying to create change,\nwe build that change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345801,"text":"So here's a select number of projects."},{"time":349464,"text":"Kosovo."},{"time":351670,"text":"This is Kosovo in '99."},{"time":353707,"text":"We did an open design\ncompetition, like I said."},{"time":356581,"text":"It led to a whole variety of ideas."},{"time":358999,"text":"And this wasn't about emergency shelter,"},{"time":360941,"text":"but transitional shelter\nthat would last five to 10 years,"},{"time":364487,"text":"that would be placed next to the land\nthe resident lived in,"},{"time":368520,"text":"and that they would rebuild\ntheir own home."},{"time":370671,"text":"This wasn't imposing\nan architecture on a community;"},{"time":373373,"text":"this was giving them\nthe tools and the space"},{"time":376519,"text":"to allow them to rebuild and regrow\nthe way they want to."},{"time":381287,"text":"We had from the sublime\nto the ridiculous, but they worked."},{"time":384231,"text":"This is an inflatable hemp house.\nIt was built; it works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389600,"text":"This is a shipping container."},{"time":392680,"text":"Built and works."},{"time":394364,"text":"And a whole variety of ideas"},{"time":395738,"text":"that not only dealt with\narchitectural building,"},{"time":399269,"text":"but also the issues of governance,"},{"time":400967,"text":"and the idea of creating communities\nthrough complex networks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404402,"text":"So we've engaged not just designers,"},{"time":406248,"text":"but also a whole variety\nof technology-based professionals."},{"time":411797,"text":"Using rubble from destroyed homes\nto create new homes."},{"time":415428,"text":"Using straw bale construction,\ncreating heat walls."},{"time":421734,"text":"And then something remarkable\nhappened in '99."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423926,"text":"We went to Africa originally\nto look at the housing issue."},{"time":428048,"text":"Within three days, we realized\nthe problem was not housing;"},{"time":430859,"text":"it was the growing pandemic of HIV/AIDS."},{"time":433970,"text":"And it wasn't doctors telling us this;"},{"time":435847,"text":"it was actual villagers\nthat we were staying with."},{"time":438871,"text":"And so we came up with the bright idea"},{"time":441507,"text":"that instead of getting people to walk\n10, 15 kilometers to see doctors,"},{"time":445726,"text":"you get the doctors to the people."},{"time":447589,"text":"And we started engaging\nthe medical community,"},{"time":450481,"text":"and you know, we thought\nwe were real bright sparks --"},{"time":453608,"text":"\"We've come up with this great idea:"},{"time":455378,"text":"mobile health clinics, widely distributed\nthroughout sub-Saharan Africa.\""},{"time":460349,"text":"And the medical community there said,"},{"time":462817,"text":"\"We've said this for the last decade."},{"time":465307,"text":"We know this. We just don't know\nhow to show this.\""},{"time":468409,"text":"So in a way, we had taken pre-existing\nneeds and shown solutions."},{"time":474177,"text":"And so again, we had a whole variety\nof ideas that came in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479173,"text":"This one I personally love,"},{"time":481040,"text":"because the idea is that architecture\nis not just about solutions,"},{"time":484365,"text":"but about raising awareness."},{"time":486068,"text":"This is a kenaf clinic."},{"time":488506,"text":"You get seed and you grow it\nin a plot of land,"},{"time":491600,"text":"and it grows 14 feet in a month."},{"time":495293,"text":"And on the fourth week, the doctors\ncome and they mow out an area,"},{"time":498469,"text":"put a tensile structure on the top,"},{"time":500572,"text":"and when the doctors\nhave finished treating"},{"time":503268,"text":"and seeing patients and villagers,"},{"time":507013,"text":"you cut down the clinic and you eat it."},{"time":508909,"text":"It's an eat-your-own-clinic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510600,"text":"So it's dealing with the fact\nthat if you have AIDS,"},{"time":513978,"text":"you also need to have nutrition rates,"},{"time":515946,"text":"and the idea of nutrition is as important"},{"time":518826,"text":"as getting antiretrovirals out there."},{"time":520684,"text":"So you know, this is a serious solution."},{"time":524043,"text":"This one I love."},{"time":525223,"text":"The idea is it's not just a clinic,\nit's a community center."},{"time":528072,"text":"This looked at setting up trade routes"},{"time":530119,"text":"and economic engines within the community,"},{"time":532208,"text":"so it can be a self-sustaining project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534446,"text":"Every one of these projects\nis sustainable."},{"time":537176,"text":"That's not because\nI'm a tree-hugging green person."},{"time":540504,"text":"It's because when you live\non four dollars a day,"},{"time":542852,"text":"you're living on survival\nand you have to be sustainable."},{"time":546227,"text":"You have to know where\nyour energy is coming from,"},{"time":548601,"text":"you have to know where\nyour resource is coming from,"},{"time":551077,"text":"and you have to keep the maintenance down."},{"time":553115,"text":"So this is about getting\nan economic engine,"},{"time":555227,"text":"and then at night,\nit turns into a movie theater."},{"time":557544,"text":"So it's not an AIDS clinic.\nIt's a community center."},{"time":562695,"text":"So you can see ideas."},{"time":564909,"text":"And these ideas developed into prototypes,"},{"time":567600,"text":"and they were eventually built."},{"time":569415,"text":"And currently, as of this year,"},{"time":570946,"text":"there are clinics rolling out\nin Nigeria and Kenya."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576976,"text":"From that, we also developed Siyathemba."},{"time":580563,"text":"The community came to us and said,"},{"time":582248,"text":"\"The problem is that the girls\ndon't have education.\""},{"time":585295,"text":"And we're working in an area"},{"time":586669,"text":"where young women\nbetween the ages of 16 and 24"},{"time":588922,"text":"have a 50 percent HIV/AIDS rate."},{"time":592317,"text":"And that's not\nbecause they're promiscuous,"},{"time":595103,"text":"it's because there's no knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596777,"text":"And so we decided to look\nat the idea of sports,"},{"time":599800,"text":"and create a youth sports center"},{"time":601666,"text":"that doubled as an HIV/AIDS\noutreach center,"},{"time":604488,"text":"and the coaches of the girls' team\nwere also trained doctors."},{"time":608345,"text":"So that there would be a very slow way\nof developing confidence in health care."},{"time":615514,"text":"And we picked nine finalists,"},{"time":617983,"text":"and then those nine finalists were\ndistributed throughout the entire region,"},{"time":621816,"text":"and then the community\npicked their design."},{"time":623967,"text":"They said, this is our design,"},{"time":625919,"text":"because it's not only\nabout engaging a community;"},{"time":628243,"text":"it's about empowering a community,"},{"time":629961,"text":"and about getting them to be\na part of the rebuilding process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634738,"text":"So, the winning design is here."},{"time":638600,"text":"And then, of course,\nwe actually go and work"},{"time":640687,"text":"with the community and the clients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642394,"text":"So this is the designer."},{"time":643616,"text":"He's out there working\nwith the first ever women's soccer team"},{"time":646593,"text":"in KwaZulu-Natal, Siyathemba."},{"time":649871,"text":"And they can tell it better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653014,"text":"(A cappella singing\nin a South African language)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":674505,"text":"Video: Well, my name is Cee Cee Mkhonza."},{"time":676514,"text":"I work at the Africa Centre,\nI'm an IT user consultant."},{"time":679484,"text":"I'm also the national football player\nfor South Africa, Banyana Banyana."},{"time":683992,"text":"And I also play in the Vodacom League,\nfor the team called Tembisa,"},{"time":690751,"text":"which has now changed to Siyathemba."},{"time":694061,"text":"This is our home ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696712,"text":"Cameron Sinclair: I'm going to show that\nlater because I'm running out of time."},{"time":700475,"text":"I can see Chris looking at me slyly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702820,"text":"This was a connection,\njust a meeting with somebody"},{"time":705781,"text":"who wanted to develop Africa's first\ntelemedicine center, in Tanzania."},{"time":710553,"text":"And we met, literally,\na couple of months ago."},{"time":712815,"text":"We've already developed a design."},{"time":714426,"text":"The team is over there,\nworking in partnership."},{"time":716657,"text":"This was a matchmaking,\nthanks to a couple of TEDsters --"},{"time":719965,"text":"Sun [Microsystems],\nCheryl Heller and Andrew Zolli,"},{"time":723539,"text":"who connected me\nwith this amazing African woman."},{"time":725922,"text":"And we start construction in June,\nand it will be opened by TEDGlobal."},{"time":729466,"text":"So when you come to TEDGlobal,\nyou can check it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732537,"text":"But what we're known probably most for\nis dealing with disasters and development,"},{"time":736587,"text":"and we've been involved\nin a lot of issues,"},{"time":738650,"text":"such as the tsunami\nand also things like Hurricane Katrina."},{"time":744861,"text":"This is a 370-dollar shelter\nthat can be easily assembled."},{"time":752904,"text":"This is a community-designed\ncommunity center."},{"time":757904,"text":"And what that means is we actually\nlive and work with the community,"},{"time":761824,"text":"and they're part of the design process."},{"time":766296,"text":"The kids actually get\ninvolved in mapping out"},{"time":768858,"text":"where the community center should be."},{"time":771932,"text":"And then eventually, the community,\nthrough skills training,"},{"time":775423,"text":"end up building the building with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777984,"text":"Here is another school."},{"time":780096,"text":"This is what the UN gave these guys\nfor six months -- 12 plastic tarps."},{"time":785136,"text":"This was in August."},{"time":786415,"text":"This was the replacement;\nthat's supposed to last for two years."},{"time":789463,"text":"When the rain comes down,\nyou can't hear a thing,"},{"time":791789,"text":"and in the summer,\nit's about 140 degrees inside."},{"time":794127,"text":"So we said, if the rain's coming\ndown, let's get fresh water."},{"time":797600,"text":"So every one of our schools\nhas a rainwater collection system."},{"time":800654,"text":"Very low cost: three classrooms\nand rainwater collection is 5,000 dollars."},{"time":807180,"text":"This was raised by hot chocolate\nsales in Atlanta."},{"time":812311,"text":"It's built by the parents of the kids."},{"time":814260,"text":"The kids are out there on-site,\nbuilding the buildings."},{"time":816911,"text":"And it opened a couple of weeks ago,"},{"time":818696,"text":"and there's 600 kids\nthat are now using the schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821299,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":828127,"text":"So, disaster hits home."},{"time":831090,"text":"We see the bad stories\non CNN and Fox and all that,"},{"time":835843,"text":"but we don't see the good stories."},{"time":837651,"text":"Here is a community that got together,\nand they said \"no\" to waiting."},{"time":841794,"text":"They formed a partnership,\na diverse partnership of players,"},{"time":845064,"text":"to actually map out East Biloxi,"},{"time":847199,"text":"to figure out who's getting involved."},{"time":849087,"text":"We've had over 1,500 volunteers\nrebuilding, rehabbing homes."},{"time":853600,"text":"Figuring out what FEMA regulations are,"},{"time":855809,"text":"not waiting for them to dictate\nto us how you should rebuild."},{"time":859658,"text":"Working with residents,"},{"time":860921,"text":"getting them out of their homes,\nso they don't get ill."},{"time":864360,"text":"This is what they're\ncleaning up on their own."},{"time":867983,"text":"Designing housing."},{"time":869160,"text":"This house is going in\nin a couple of weeks."},{"time":871301,"text":"This is a rehabbed home,\ndone in four days."},{"time":874433,"text":"This is a utility room\nfor a woman who is on a walker."},{"time":878600,"text":"She's 70 years old.\nThis is what FEMA gave her."},{"time":882026,"text":"600 bucks, happened two days ago."},{"time":885000,"text":"We put together, very quickly, a washroom."},{"time":887880,"text":"It's built, it's running and she just\nstarted a business today,"},{"time":890897,"text":"where she's washing\nother people's clothes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":892944,"text":"These are the Calhouns."},{"time":896600,"text":"They're photographers who had documented\nthe Lower Ninth for the last 40 years."},{"time":900941,"text":"That was their home,\nand these are the photographs they took."},{"time":903890,"text":"And we're helping, working with them\nto create a new building."},{"time":907533,"text":"Projects we've done."},{"time":909183,"text":"Projects we've been a part of, support."},{"time":911980,"text":"Why don't aid agencies do this?"},{"time":915716,"text":"This is the UN tent."},{"time":918406,"text":"This is the new UN tent,\njust introduced this year."},{"time":921351,"text":"Quick to assemble."},{"time":922854,"text":"It's got a flap -- that's the invention."},{"time":926426,"text":"It took 20 years to design this\nand get it implemented in the field."},{"time":930844,"text":"I was 12 years old."},{"time":933768,"text":"There's a problem here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936728,"text":"Luckily, we're not alone."},{"time":938712,"text":"There are hundreds and hundreds\nand hundreds and hundreds"},{"time":941600,"text":"and hundreds of architects\nand designers and inventors"},{"time":945600,"text":"around the world that are getting\ninvolved in humanitarian work."},{"time":951234,"text":"More hemp houses -- it's a theme\nin Japan, apparently."},{"time":954298,"text":"I'm not sure what they're smoking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955957,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":959671,"text":"This is a Grip Clip,\ndesigned by somebody who said,"},{"time":962402,"text":"\"All you need is some way\nto attach membrane structures"},{"time":965433,"text":"to physical support beams.\""},{"time":970942,"text":"This guy designed for NASA,\nis now doing housing."},{"time":976314,"text":"I'm going to whip through this quickly,"},{"time":978243,"text":"because I know I've got\nonly a couple of minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982165,"text":"So this is all done in the last two years."},{"time":984334,"text":"I showed you something\nthat took 20 years to do."},{"time":986985,"text":"And this is just a selection of things"},{"time":989094,"text":"that were built\nin the last couple of years."},{"time":992217,"text":"From Brazil to India,"},{"time":995167,"text":"Mexico,"},{"time":997420,"text":"Alabama,"},{"time":1001326,"text":"China,"},{"time":1003825,"text":"Israel,"},{"time":1005003,"text":"Palestine,"},{"time":1006823,"text":"Vietnam."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008306,"text":"The average age of a designer\nwho gets involved in this project is 32 --"},{"time":1012481,"text":"that's how old I am."},{"time":1013776,"text":"So it's a young --"},{"time":1016949,"text":"I just have to stop here,\nbecause Arup is in the room,"},{"time":1019621,"text":"and this is the best-designed\ntoilet in the world."},{"time":1022002,"text":"If you're ever, ever in India,\ngo use this toilet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025073,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026167,"text":"Chris Luebkeman will tell you why."},{"time":1028600,"text":"I'm sure that's how he wanted\nto spend the party."},{"time":1036548,"text":"But the future is not going to be\nthe sky-scraping cities of New York,"},{"time":1039882,"text":"but this."},{"time":1041057,"text":"And when you look at this, you see crisis."},{"time":1043167,"text":"What I see is many, many inventors."},{"time":1046469,"text":"One billion people live in abject poverty."},{"time":1048628,"text":"We hear about them all the time."},{"time":1050296,"text":"Four billion live in growing\nbut fragile economies."},{"time":1054680,"text":"One in seven live\nin unplanned settlements."},{"time":1057462,"text":"If we do nothing about the housing crisis\nthat's about to happen,"},{"time":1060636,"text":"in 20 years, one in three people\nwill live in an unplanned settlement"},{"time":1064215,"text":"or a refugee camp."},{"time":1065502,"text":"Look left, look right:\none of you will be there."},{"time":1069080,"text":"How do we improve the living standards\nof five billion people?"},{"time":1072866,"text":"With 10 million solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075176,"text":"So I wish to develop a community"},{"time":1076903,"text":"that actively embraces\ninnovative and sustainable design"},{"time":1080500,"text":"to improve the living\nconditions for everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083497,"text":"Chris Anderson: Wait a sec --\nthat's your wish?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085839,"text":"CS: That's my wish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087014,"text":"CA: That's his wish!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1088189,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101303,"text":"CS: We started Architecture for Humanity\nwith 700 dollars and a website."},{"time":1105707,"text":"So Chris somehow decided\nto give me 100,000."},{"time":1109783,"text":"So why not this many people?"},{"time":1112983,"text":"Open-source architecture is the way to go."},{"time":1115452,"text":"You have a diverse community\nof participants --"},{"time":1118563,"text":"and we're not just talking\nabout inventors and designers,"},{"time":1121460,"text":"but we're talking about the funding model."},{"time":1123603,"text":"My role is not as a designer;"},{"time":1125405,"text":"it's as a conduit between the design world\nand the humanitarian world."},{"time":1128914,"text":"And what we need is something\nthat replicates me globally,"},{"time":1133692,"text":"because I haven't slept in seven years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1136060,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1138600,"text":"Secondly, what will this thing be?"},{"time":1141453,"text":"Designers want to respond\nto issues of humanitarian crisis,"},{"time":1145357,"text":"but they don't want\nsome company in the West"},{"time":1148332,"text":"taking their idea\nand basically profiting from it."},{"time":1151007,"text":"So Creative Commons has developed\nthe Developing Nations license."},{"time":1155180,"text":"And what that means\nis that a designer can --"},{"time":1157594,"text":"The Siyathemba project I showed"},{"time":1159451,"text":"was the first ever building to have\na Creative Commons license on it."},{"time":1163443,"text":"As soon as that is built, anyone\nin Africa or any developing nation"},{"time":1168600,"text":"can take the construction documents\nand replicate it for free."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1173657,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1178233,"text":"So why not allow designers\nthe opportunity to do this,"},{"time":1181176,"text":"but still protect their rights here?"},{"time":1183478,"text":"We want to have a community\nwhere you can upload ideas,"},{"time":1187507,"text":"and those ideas can be tested\nin an earthquake, in flood,"},{"time":1191731,"text":"in all sorts of austere environments."},{"time":1194075,"text":"The reason that's important"},{"time":1195836,"text":"is I don't want to wait\nfor the next Katrina"},{"time":1197917,"text":"to find out if my house works."},{"time":1200672,"text":"That's too late, we need to do it now."},{"time":1203172,"text":"So doing that globally --"},{"time":1204530,"text":"and I want this whole thing\nto work multi-lingually."},{"time":1210044,"text":"When you look at the face of an architect,\nmost people think a gray-haired white guy."},{"time":1214151,"text":"I don't see that;\nI see the face of the world."},{"time":1216890,"text":"So I want everyone\nfrom all over the planet"},{"time":1218974,"text":"to be able to be a part\nof this design and development."},{"time":1222942,"text":"The idea of needs-based competitions --"},{"time":1225015,"text":"XPRIZE for the other 98 percent,\nif you want to call it that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1229749,"text":"We also want to look\nat ways of matchmaking"},{"time":1232067,"text":"and putting funding partners together,"},{"time":1234208,"text":"and the idea of integrating\nmanufacturers --"},{"time":1236574,"text":"fab labs in every country."},{"time":1238193,"text":"When I hear about the $100 laptop\nand it's going to educate every child --"},{"time":1242032,"text":"educate every designer in the world."},{"time":1244057,"text":"Put one in every favela,\nevery slum settlement."},{"time":1248591,"text":"Because you know what?\nInnovation will happen."},{"time":1250853,"text":"And I need to know that.\nIt's called the leap-back."},{"time":1253259,"text":"We talk about leapfrog technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1255413,"text":"I write with Worldchanging,"},{"time":1256818,"text":"and the one thing\nwe've been talking about is,"},{"time":1258995,"text":"I learn more on the ground\nthan I've ever learned here."},{"time":1261606,"text":"So let's take those ideas,\nadapt them, and we can use them."},{"time":1267428,"text":"These ideas are supposed to be adaptable;"},{"time":1270873,"text":"they should have\nthe potential for evolution;"},{"time":1274634,"text":"they should be developed\nby every nation in the world"},{"time":1277154,"text":"and useful for every nation in the world."},{"time":1279837,"text":"What will it take?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1281430,"text":"There should be a sheet."},{"time":1282628,"text":"I don't have time to read this,\nbecause I'm going to be yanked off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1286160,"text":"CA: Let's just leave it up for a sec."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1288454,"text":"CS: Well, what will it take?\nYou guys are smart."},{"time":1292094,"text":"So it's going to take a lot\nof computing power,"},{"time":1294982,"text":"because I want the idea\nthat any laptop anywhere in the world"},{"time":1298105,"text":"can plug into the system"},{"time":1299500,"text":"and be able to not only participate\nin developing these designs,"},{"time":1303086,"text":"but utilize the designs."},{"time":1304865,"text":"Also, a process of reviewing the designs."},{"time":1308646,"text":"I want every Arup engineer\nin the world to check and make sure"},{"time":1312082,"text":"that we're doing stuff that's standing,"},{"time":1313975,"text":"because those guys\nare the best in the world."},{"time":1316140,"text":"Plug."},{"time":1317909,"text":"And so, you know, I want these --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1321490,"text":"I just should note: I have two laptops\nand one of them is there,"},{"time":1325268,"text":"and that has 3000 designs on it."},{"time":1327775,"text":"If I drop that laptop ..."},{"time":1330752,"text":"What happens?"},{"time":1332226,"text":"So it's important to have\nthese proven ideas put up there,"},{"time":1335218,"text":"easy to use, easy to get ahold of."},{"time":1341044,"text":"My mom once said, \"There's nothing worse\nthan being all mouth and no trousers.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1344843,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1346374,"text":"I'm fed up of talking about making change."},{"time":1349549,"text":"You only make it by doing it."},{"time":1351843,"text":"We've changed FEMA guidelines;\nwe've changed public policy;"},{"time":1355447,"text":"we've changed international response --\nbased on building things."},{"time":1359885,"text":"So for me, it's important that we create\na real conduit for innovation,"},{"time":1364258,"text":"and that it's free innovation."},{"time":1365926,"text":"Think of free culture --\nthis is free innovation."},{"time":1370858,"text":"Somebody said this a couple of years back."},{"time":1375138,"text":"I will give points for those who know it."},{"time":1377299,"text":"But I think the man was maybe\n25 years too early."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1383584,"text":"So let's do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1385833,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1387010,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}